00:00:40.908 --> 00:00:43.210
Let's begin with our first session.

00:00:43.277 --> 00:00:45.679
I'll introduce you to
subscription offer codes,

00:00:45.746 --> 00:00:49.016
explain how they work, and describe
the ways you can start using them

00:00:49.082 --> 00:00:51.084
to grow and retain your business.

00:00:51.785 --> 00:00:55.022
We're excited to share that
offer codes are now available,

00:00:55.088 --> 00:00:58.325
and you can begin generating codes
in App Store Connect.

00:00:58.792 --> 00:01:01.695
Offer codes are complementary
to our other offer types

00:01:01.762 --> 00:01:03.864
that you may already be familiar with

00:01:03.931 --> 00:01:06.099
but provide even more flexibility,

00:01:06.166 --> 00:01:10.404
giving you the ability to merchandise
subscription offers outside of your app.

00:01:11.772 --> 00:01:15.943
Offer codes can help you acquire,
retain, and win back subscribers.

00:01:16.443 --> 00:01:19.780
They are unique,
one-time use alphanumeric codes

00:01:19.847 --> 00:01:24.151
that you can choose to distribute across
both your online and offline channels.

00:01:24.852 --> 00:01:26.186
Once distributed,

00:01:26.253 --> 00:01:29.957
your customers can seamlessly redeem
offer codes in the App Store

00:01:30.023 --> 00:01:33.327
or directly in your app
when using the StoreKit API,

00:01:33.393 --> 00:01:36.096
which David is going to
talk about more shortly.

00:01:36.163 --> 00:01:38.065
At the end of the offer period,

00:01:38.131 --> 00:01:40.834
the subscription auto-renews
at the standard price,

00:01:40.901 --> 00:01:44.137
unless a subscriber cancels
or turns off auto-renewal.

00:01:44.972 --> 00:01:48.008
There are a number of different ways
offer codes can be used,

00:01:48.075 --> 00:01:51.545
and you have the flexibility
to distribute them however you like.

00:01:52.179 --> 00:01:55.148
Codes can be distributed
in your digital marketing channels,

00:01:55.215 --> 00:01:58.986
such as email,
to acquire or win back subscribers.

00:01:59.052 --> 00:02:02.256
For example, a sports league
might email an offer code

00:02:02.322 --> 00:02:05.158
for an extended free trial
to season ticket holders.

00:02:05.592 --> 00:02:07.794
As an add-on where a subscription service

00:02:07.861 --> 00:02:10.564
complements a physical good or service.

00:02:10.631 --> 00:02:13.267
For example, an exercise bike company

00:02:13.333 --> 00:02:16.170
could include an extended trial
for virtual classes

00:02:16.236 --> 00:02:17.838
with the purchase of a bike.

00:02:18.305 --> 00:02:20.307
In physical retail or at events,

00:02:20.374 --> 00:02:22.676
including industry conferences.

00:02:22.743 --> 00:02:26.513
For example, a music service
could hand out flyers with offer codes

00:02:26.580 --> 00:02:28.382
at concerts or festivals.

00:02:29.216 --> 00:02:31.318
Distributed via third-party partners

00:02:31.385 --> 00:02:35.222
as part of co-marketing campaigns
and partner-marketing initiatives.

00:02:35.923 --> 00:02:38.458
A mobile phone carrier
might distribute offer codes

00:02:38.525 --> 00:02:41.828
for a video streaming service
to its customers via email.

00:02:43.397 --> 00:02:46.900
Codes can also be distributed by
customer support teams

00:02:46.967 --> 00:02:49.102
who might give a customer
with a service issue

00:02:49.169 --> 00:02:50.904
a free or discounted period

00:02:50.971 --> 00:02:54.308
in lieu of sending the customer
to AppleCare for a refund.

00:02:55.843 --> 00:02:58.078
You will create codes in App Store Connect

00:02:58.145 --> 00:03:01.148
and have the ability to configure
your offer code campaigns

00:03:01.215 --> 00:03:04.117
for new, existing,
and/or lapsed subscribers.

00:03:04.785 --> 00:03:08.555
You can create up to 10 active offers
per subscription SKU

00:03:08.622 --> 00:03:13.794
and have the ability to create batches
of between 500 to 25,000 codes,

00:03:13.861 --> 00:03:17.764
up to a maximum of 150,000 per app,
per quarter.

00:03:18.532 --> 00:03:21.602
You'll be able to choose
each batch's expiration date,

00:03:21.668 --> 00:03:25.005
up to a maximum of six months
from the date of creation.

00:03:26.707 --> 00:03:29.743
After you've configured
and distributed your codes,

00:03:29.810 --> 00:03:32.546
customers can redeem directly
on the App Store

00:03:32.613 --> 00:03:35.949
through the Redeem Gift Card flow
found in the account page

00:03:36.016 --> 00:03:39.486
or within your app
by using Apple's provided UI.

00:03:40.220 --> 00:03:43.190
The Apple UI
handles the full redemption experience,

00:03:43.257 --> 00:03:45.592
and if an app isn't already installed,

00:03:45.659 --> 00:03:48.729
the user will first be prompted
to download the app.

00:03:48.795 --> 00:03:51.265
Let's look at that customer journey
in more detail.

00:03:51.899 --> 00:03:54.635
If you're distributing
your offer codes offline,

00:03:54.701 --> 00:03:57.704
such as at an event
or with a physical product,

00:03:57.771 --> 00:04:01.108
the customer can seamlessly redeem
the code from within your app

00:04:01.175 --> 00:04:03.977
when you use
the presentCodeRedemptionSheet.

00:04:04.845 --> 00:04:07.381
You might consider adding
a Redeem Code button

00:04:07.447 --> 00:04:10.184
to your app's paywall,
like the example here.

00:04:11.385 --> 00:04:14.288
After a customer taps
your custom Redeem button,

00:04:14.788 --> 00:04:18.959
the system automatically provides
a series of code-redemption screens,

00:04:19.026 --> 00:04:21.461
the first being the code input page.

00:04:21.962 --> 00:04:25.732
Once a customer types in the code
and that code is valid,

00:04:25.799 --> 00:04:28.035
the offer details page is shown.

00:04:28.802 --> 00:04:31.271
If for any reason the code isn't valid,

00:04:31.338 --> 00:04:33.473
the customer will see
a clear error message

00:04:33.540 --> 00:04:36.176
explaining why the offer
is unavailable to them.

00:04:38.378 --> 00:04:41.281
Now, if you're distributing on
digital marketing channels,

00:04:41.348 --> 00:04:42.683
such as email,

00:04:42.749 --> 00:04:45.352
each code will have
an associated deep link URL

00:04:45.419 --> 00:04:47.421
for distribution on these channels.

00:04:48.622 --> 00:04:50.791
You'll be able to use a unique URL

00:04:50.858 --> 00:04:55.062
to seamlessly deep link the customer
from your email to the redemption flow.

00:04:55.128 --> 00:04:56.697
So, in this example,

00:04:56.763 --> 00:05:00.267
Ocean Journal is offering
a one-month free trial via email,

00:05:00.334 --> 00:05:02.836
and once the customer taps Try It Now,

00:05:02.903 --> 00:05:05.305
they're deep linked
into the redemption flow.

00:05:06.874 --> 00:05:09.209
If the app isn't already installed,

00:05:09.276 --> 00:05:12.679
the customer will first be prompted
to download the app.

00:05:13.914 --> 00:05:17.851
Once the app has downloaded,
the offer details sheet will appear

00:05:17.918 --> 00:05:20.487
and the customer
can then redeem and subscribe.

00:05:20.988 --> 00:05:24.057
You'll notice the code input step
isn't required here,

00:05:24.124 --> 00:05:26.193
as the code is part of the URL.

00:05:27.060 --> 00:05:29.963
However you decide to distribute
your offer codes,

00:05:30.030 --> 00:05:33.033
we recommend communicating
the code expiration date

00:05:33.100 --> 00:05:36.270
alongside other eligibility
or availability limits

00:05:36.336 --> 00:05:38.338
in your marketing communications.

00:05:39.173 --> 00:05:43.210
Offer codes can also be utilized
to cross-promote subscription apps.

00:05:44.144 --> 00:05:45.379
In this example,

00:05:45.445 --> 00:05:48.382
offer codes are used
to assist with migrating customers

00:05:48.448 --> 00:05:51.218
from an app that's being sunset
to a new app.

00:05:52.019 --> 00:05:54.755
ZenWell clearly communicates
that it is closing

00:05:54.821 --> 00:05:57.624
and the customer's current subscription
will expire.

00:05:58.325 --> 00:06:00.827
ZenWell then uses an offer code deep link

00:06:00.894 --> 00:06:05.098
to give those customers a special offer
to a new app, Serenely,

00:06:05.165 --> 00:06:09.369
and since they're using a deep link URL
associated with each code,

00:06:09.436 --> 00:06:12.472
the customer
can seamlessly download the new app

00:06:12.539 --> 00:06:14.608
and then redeem and subscribe.

00:06:15.909 --> 00:06:18.846
Additionally,
offer codes can be used offline

00:06:18.912 --> 00:06:21.481
at events or industry conferences.

00:06:21.548 --> 00:06:25.385
In this example,
the unique offer code is printed on flyers

00:06:25.452 --> 00:06:27.788
which are handed out at a music festival,

00:06:27.855 --> 00:06:30.591
giving attendees
a three-month free subscription

00:06:30.657 --> 00:06:32.492
to a music streaming service.

00:06:33.060 --> 00:06:35.963
Later, the same app
sends lapsed subscribers

00:06:36.029 --> 00:06:40.901
an offer code via email for an additional
one month free to retry the service.

00:06:42.736 --> 00:06:46.240
Offer codes are complementary to
our other offer types

00:06:46.306 --> 00:06:48.842
but now give you much more flexibility.

00:06:48.909 --> 00:06:51.578
Each offer type has a distinct use case.

00:06:53.113 --> 00:06:56.416
So let's quickly summarize
the three different offer types.

00:06:56.917 --> 00:06:59.520
Offer codes can be used for acquiring new,

00:06:59.586 --> 00:07:01.855
retaining, and winning back subscribers.

00:07:02.723 --> 00:07:04.725
Offer codes give you the unique ability

00:07:04.791 --> 00:07:09.796
to merchandise your subscription offers
outside of your app, online and offline,

00:07:09.863 --> 00:07:12.432
but with a seamless customer experience.

00:07:14.034 --> 00:07:17.271
You can configure
10 active offers per subscription,

00:07:17.337 --> 00:07:21.241
with a limit of 150,000 codes
per app, per quarter.

00:07:22.609 --> 00:07:25.946
And customers can redeem
one code per active offer.

00:07:27.281 --> 00:07:28.949
Offer codes are available now,

00:07:29.016 --> 00:07:31.485
and we can't wait to see
how you use this new feature

00:07:31.552 --> 00:07:33.820
to acquire and retain subscribers.

